text: Donald C. Bolduc (born May 8, 1962)Retired General to Run for New Hampshire Senate Seat is an American politician and retired United States Army brigadier general. He was the Republican nominee for the United States Senate in the 2022 election, but lost to incumbent Democrat Maggie Hassan. Bolduc was also a Republican candidate for the U.S. Senate in 2020 but did not win the primary. ==References== Category:1962 births Category:Living people Category:Politicians from New Hampshire Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians
